CNCP v1 24871
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11273: v-bind in SSR with dev server fails to resolve imported objects",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:38.796966+00:00",
  "text": "v-bind in SSR with dev server fails to resolve imported objects\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.4.31\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\n* [Playground](https://play.vuejs.org/#__SSR__)\r\n* Repo: https://github.com/bcdanieldickison/ssr-test\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nWhen rendering SSR inside of the vite dev server with `vite.ssrLoadModule`, `v-bind` inside of `<style>` fails when referencing an `import`-ed object from `<script setup>`. Simply assigning the object to a new `const` at the script scope works around the issue, as does doing a production SSR build.\r\n\r\nApp.vue:\r\n```vue\r\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\r\nimport Color from './Color'\r\nconst C = Color\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<template>\r\n  <h1>Hello</h1>\r\n</template>\r\n\r\n<style>\r\nh1 {\r\n  /* this fails: */\r\n  color: v-bind(\"Color.red\");\r\n  \r\n  /* this works: */\r\n  /* color: v-bind(\"C.red\"); */\r\n}\r\n</style>\r\n```\r\n\r\nssr-fail.js:\r\n```js\r\nimport { exit } from 'process'\r\nimport { createServer as createViteServer } from 'vite'\r\n\r\nconst vite = await createViteServer({\r\n  server: { middlewareMode: true },\r\n  appType: 'custom'\r\n})\r\nconst { render } = await vite.ssrLoadModule('/src/entry-server.js')\r\nconst appHtml = await render('/')\r\nconsole.log(appHtml)\r\nexit(0)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ npm test\r\n<h1 style=\"--7a7a37b1-C\\.red:#ff00ee;\">Hello</h1>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ npm run test\r\n/Users/daniel/bc/src/ssr-test/src/App.vue:26\r\n    \"--7a7a37b1-Color\\\\.red\": $setup.Color.red\r\n                                           ^\r\n\r\nTypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'red')\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nSystem:\r\n    OS: macOS 14.4.1\r\n    CPU: (10) arm64 Apple M1 Pro\r\n    Memory: 1.50 GB / 32.00 GB\r\n    Shell: 5.9 - /bin/zsh\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 21.7.2 - /opt/homebrew/bin/node\r\n    npm: 10.8.1 - /opt/homebrew/bin/npm\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 126.0.6478.127\r\n    Safari: 17.4.1\r\n    Safari Technology Preview: 18.0\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    vue: ^3.4.29 => 3.4.31\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\nWe maintain a design-system module with various constants for color tokens. The most natural way to use these in our app components leads to this error in our dev environment.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "has workaround",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
